@karuturi I would have to look at that code to know.  Openswan was removed and replaced with Strongswan in 4.10, so the implementation is different. 

If I remember correctly, they were just reloading the ipsec config in 4.9, but the code did bounce the xl2tpd service on change. In testing yesterday, stopping the xl2tpd service and starting it again was casing issues where the tunnel could not be found when it came back up. 

I can open a similar PR against 4.9, but I don't have a 4.9 environment right now, so I can't test it. Should I create a new PR for it and ask for others to validate it?
